# Presentation Outline — Nobat One

## Slide 1 — Title
Nobat One  
Universal Queue Management Platform

## Slide 2 — Problem
Manual queues are inefficient and frustrating.

## Slide 3 — Solution
Join queue remotely, track wait time, manage flow digitally.

## Slide 4 — Target Users
Customers, business staff, business owners.

## Slide 5 — Requirements
5+ functional requirements, measurable NFRs, 8 user stories, 3 use cases.

## Slide 6 — Architecture
C4 context, container, component, and ERD.

## Slide 7 — API
Main endpoints for customer and dashboard features.

## Slide 8 — UI/UX Mockups
Home, service page, join queue, queue status, business dashboard.

## Slide 9 — Demo
Working local prototype.

## Slide 10 — Process
GitHub issues, project board, PR workflow, lessons learned.

## Slide 11 — Roadmap
MVP -> reservations -> analytics -> AI wait-time prediction.

## Slide 12 — Closing
Why Nobat One matters and what comes next.
